# Project Structure Guide

This Next.js project follows a specific structure to maintain scalability and organization:

## Core Directories
- [app/](mdc:app/) - Contains all Next.js app router pages and layouts
- [components/](mdc:components/) - Reusable React components
- [lib/](mdc:lib/) - Utility functions, hooks, and shared logic
- [prisma/](mdc:prisma/) - Database schema and migrations
- [public/](mdc:public/) - Static assets
- [scripts/](mdc:scripts/) - Build and utility scripts

## Key Configuration Files
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - TailwindCSS configuration
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - Shadcn UI configuration
- [prisma/schema.prisma](mdc:prisma/schema.prisma) - Database schema

## Coding Standards
1. Use TypeScript for all new files
2. Follow the component structure:
   - Page components in `app/`
   - Reusable components in `components/`
   - Utility functions in `lib/`
3. Use Tailwind CSS for styling
4. Implement Shadcn UI components when possible
5. Follow accessibility best practices